description.narrative: Supporting International Family Planning Organizations 2: Sustainable Networks (SIFPO 2) will increase the use of FP services globally through strengthening selected international Family Planning/Reproductive Health (FP/RH) organizations which have a global reach and an extensive, multi-country network of FP/RH and other health platforms, in order to achieve maximum program impact and synergies.

Organizaciones internacionales favorables 2 de la planificación familiar: Redes sostenibles (SIFPO 2) aumentará el uso de los servicios del punto de congelación global con fortalecer las organizaciones de la planificación familiar internacional seleccionada/de la salud reproductiva (FP/RH) que tienen un alcance global y una red extensa, plurinacional de FP/RH y otras plataformas de la salud, para alcanzar impacto y sinergias máximos del programa.

Organizações internacionais de apoio 2 do planeamento familiar: As redes sustentáveis (SIFPO 2) aumentarão o uso de serviços do FP globalmente com do reforço das organizações do planeamento familiar internacional selecionado/saúde reprodutiva (FP/RH) que têm um alcance global e um extensivo, da rede do multi-país de FP/RH e das outras plataformas da saúde, a fim conseguir o impacto e sinergias máximos do programa.

Organismes internationaux de soutien 2 de planification des naissances : Réseaux viables (SIFPO 2) augmentera l'utilisation des services de point de gel globalement en renforçant les organismes de planification des naissances internationale choisie/santé génésique (FP/RH) qui ont une portée globale et un réseau étendu et multinational de FP/RH et d'autres plates-formes de santé, afin de réaliser l'impact et les synergies maximum de programme.

Objectives for Nepal: The goal of the project is to accelerate the ability of governments, KP organizations, and private-sector providers to collaboratively plan, deliver, and optimize services that reduce HIV transmission among KPs and extend life for those who are living with HIV. The project has three result areas: 1: Increased availability of comprehensive prevention, care, and treatment services, including reliable coverage across the continuum of care for KPs. 2: Demand for comprehensive prevention, care, and treatment services among KPs enhanced and sustained. 3: Strengthened systems for planning, monitoring, evaluating, and ensuring the quality of programs for KPs.
